Hub: Win10/192.10.1.10
Node1ï¼šWin10 with chrome/192.10.1.101
Node2: RedHat Linux 7 with Firefox/192.10.1.102

Steps:
0.develop test scripts for chrome and firefox.
1.download selenium-server-standalone-3.13.0.jar from selenium offical website
2.download webdriver: gecko driver and chrome driver associated with web browsers and operation systems.
3.on hub, run cmd:
 java -jar selenium-server-standalone-3.13.0.jar -role hub
4.on node1, run cmd:
java -Dwebdriver.chrome.driver="xxxx\chromedriver.exe" -jar selenium-server-standalone-3.13.0.jar -role node -hub http:///192.10.1.10:4444/grid/register
5.on node2, run cmd:
java -Dwebdriver.gecko.driver="xxxx\gecko" -jar selenium-server-standalone-3.13.0.jar -role node -hub http:///192.10.1.10:4444/grid/register
6.on hub, open http://localhost:4444/grid/console to view registration status
7.run test scripts in step #0.
end
